From 76ecad911354c24935f7b9d99b92b55643ceb636 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Caleb Connolly <caleb.connolly@linaro.org>
Date: Thu, 8 Dec 2022 19:52:20 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 165/194] drm/panel: nt36672a: move dsi commands from
 prepare/unprepare to enable/disable

The commit 007ac0262b0d ("drm/msm/dsi: switch to DRM_PANEL_BRIDGE")
breaks panels which send DSI commands in their .unprepare callbacks.
Migrate to using .disable for that for nt36672a panel. Similarly
migrate to using .enable for that for nt36672a panel.

Co-developed-by: Joel Selvaraj <foss@joelselvaraj.com>
Signed-off-by: Joel Selvaraj <foss@joelselvaraj.com>
Signed-off-by: Caleb Connolly <caleb.connolly@linaro.org>

drm/panel: novatek-nt36672a: prepare_prev_first

This corrects the host initialisation sequence so that we can send
DSI/DCS commands in prepare().

Signed-off-by: Caleb Connolly <caleb.connolly@linaro.org>

tianma panel proper enable/disable hookup! BUT 20s video out timeout delay during boot

Signed-off-by: Joel Selvaraj <foss@joelselvaraj.com>

